; **********************************************************************************
; Leading pad object for the maize-95 backward-JMP relocation regression test.
;
; This object exists only to occupy CODE space so that the real fixture
; (test_obj_backjmp) links at a NONZERO vaddr. That is what forces mzld to
; relocate the main object's sections, which in turn is what the maize-95 fix is
; about: a backward local-label JMP must carry a relocation so its target moves
; with the section. This pad is never entered (the linked entry point is _start,
; defined GLOBAL in the main object). It is deliberately a run of NOPs followed
; by HALT: if the backward JMP is left un-relocated (the pre-fix bug), the JMP
; mis-targets a low section-relative offset that lands inside THIS pad, executes
; NOPs, HALTs, and prints nothing, so the test FAILS. That is the non-vacuity the
; card requires.
; **********************************************************************************

SECTION CODE

pad_filler:
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    NOP
    HALT
